metadata.name: Urban Flora #133
metadata.description:
Urban Flora is a generative artwork exploring interplay of natural and artificial forms created by Marcin Ignac / @marcinignac

http://marcinignac.com/projects/urban-flora/

The project was inspired by the 3/4/5G network infrastructure more and more present in the parks and greenery of our cities. Final Urban Flora transformed into a study of abandoned structures of a long forgotten civilisation.

The whole image is generative and/or procedural. Leaves are parametric, twigs and trees use the space colonisation algorithm, and the geometry is based on platonic solids transformed though series of operations.

Features determined at the time of minting:
- one of the platonic solids or a prism
- one of 15 geometry transformations
- a color theme
- leaves or detailed twigs
- leaf's spread and the amount of ridges

'g' / 'tree finger tap' - resolution and export
'drag' - rotate
'scroll' - zoom (on desktop)

Please note the project needs a decent GPU.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

--
With dedication to my wife.

metadata.name: Vestige #45
metadata.description:
Vestige /ˈvɛstɪdʒ/: a trace or remnant of something that is disappearing or no longer exists.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Vestige is a GT that creates colorful gradients by layering thousands of transparent shapes. This can sometimes take a couple of seconds (depending on your machine).

Notes on Responsiveness:

When resizing the window, refresh the sketch and it will assume the new window dimensions. Zooming in and out will require you to also refresh the page.

Hit the N button and wait a short moment to explore a different [N]ew Vestige.
Hit the M button to return to the [M]ain seed, which represents your own original Vestige . Hitting the M button to update the GT after zooming does work, however you'll have to refresh to view at the new resolution.

- Best enjoyed in fullscreen.

metadata.name: BLEND #245
metadata.description:
Blend are generative loops and animated pieces creating a shape with a digital painting effect.
The size, position and motion frequency of trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 
You can press spacebar to stop the animation.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Brussels (Belgium).  

Features :
	- Between 10 and 80 trails, impacted or not by an update of their radius and randomly filled
	- 4 directions - from North West (NW), from North East (NE), from North or from West.
	- Duration between 16 and 24 seconds
	- Amplitude of the shape on X and Y
	- Offset delay: between 0.1 and trails count, manage the delay between each trails movement
	- Noise count : number of points to create the noise effect on background
	- Background color :  color randomly get from 1 of 151 color themes

metadata.name: 0xFoif #101
metadata.description:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
NOTE TO COLLECTORS:

This token will be sold as a Dutch auction. Every 5 minutes, the price will change based on the following schedule:
20 / 15 / 10 / 5 / 2 tez

After that, the price will remain fixed at 2 tez.
If there are tokens remaining after 72 hours, they will be burnt.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

0xFoif

Inspired by Tyler Hobbs' water color studies and the splitting algorithm of 0xDrue, 0xFoif is a collection of interplay between a strong grid with clear cut splits and a blurriness introduced by multiple transparent layers.

Zürich/Quito, January 2022
❤️ pifragile

metadata.name: Cambrian Explosion #4
metadata.description: Cambrian explosion, taken from the event that happened more than 500 million years ago where major phyla that make up modern organisms rapidly emerged, explores how humans see beauty in symmetrical randomness. With the form generated by random algorithms, it uncannily mimics creatures generated by nature.

metadata.name: Dissolution #127
metadata.description:
Turning and turning in the widening gyre
The falcon cannot hear the falconer;
Things fall apart; the centre cannot hold;
Mere anarchy is loosed upon the world,
The blood-dimmed tide is loosed, and everywhere
The ceremony of innocence is drowned;
The best lack all conviction, while the worst
Are full of passionate intensity.

The Second Coming
W.B. Yeats

This work requires WebGL2.

You can export a high resolution PNG (5000x5000) by pressing the 'e' key.

Twitter: @jeffpalmer
https://jpalmer.dev
